{{Infobox lake | name = Ardleigh Reservoir | image = Ardleigh Reservoir from Wick Lane - geograph.org.uk - 55381.jpg | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Essex]] | coords = {{coord|51|54|55|N|0|57|20|E|type:waterbody_region:GB|display=inline,title}} | type = [[reservoir]] | inflow = | outflow = Salary Brook | catchment = | basin_countries = United Kingdom | length = | width = | area = {{convert|120|acre|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | islands = | cities = }} '''Ardleigh Reservoir''' is a {{convert|120|acre|m2|sing=on}} lake near [[Colchester]] in [[Essex]] constructed in the valley of the [[Salary Brook, Essex|Salary Brook]]. It supplies water both to [[Anglian Water]] and to [[Veolia Water East]]. The lake is also used for recreational activities including [[sailing]] and [[angling]]. Both game and coarse fish are present including [[Esox|pike]] and [[zander]].
Ardleigh Reservoir is also home to the University of Essex Rowing Club.
