{{Infobox organization |name = Institute of Water Modeling |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 2002 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.iwmbd.org/ Institute of Water Modeling] |remarks = }}
'''Institute of Water Modeling''' or '''IWM''',<ref>{{cite news |title=Challenges ahead for Bangladesh |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/op-ed/challenges-ahead-bangladesh-1016410 |newspaper=The Daily Star |date=18 March 2016|type=Op-ed |accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref> is a government owned-national research institute and think tank that carries out research, planning and technology transfer related to water management projects in Bangladesh and is located in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="unbx">{{cite web|title=Institute of Water Modelling|url=http://www.iwmbd.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4&Itemid=5|website=iwmbd.org|accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dhaka Could Be Underwater in a Decade|url=http://www.ipsnews.net/2016/08/dhaka-could-be-underwater-in-a-decade/|website=ipsnews.net|publisher=Inter Press Service|accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=To help climate migrants, Bangladesh takes back land from the sea |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bangladesh-clmate-land-idUSKCN0R90U220150909 |newspaper=Reuters |date=9 September 2016 |accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref>
==History== The Institute traces its origins to the [[Surface Water Simulation Modelling Programme]] which was founded 1986. It functioned under the [[Water Resources Planning Organisation]]. On 24 December 1996 the cabinet of Bangladesh Government decided to institutionalized the programme, which was renamed and established as Institute of Water Modeling in 1 August 2002.<ref name="unbx" /><ref>{{cite news |title=River erosion turns 50,000 homeless every year |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/city/river-erosion-turns-50000-homeless-every-year-1289182 |newspaper=The Daily Star |date=25 September 2016 |accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref>
